# PokiHelper: main-process helper ↔ Angular

Any new or changed automation API exposed to the Angular app must be updated **together** in this order:

1. **`PokiHelper - Electron/helper.js`** — implement and `module.exports` the function(s).
2. **`PokiHelper - Electron/main.js`** — register `ipcMain.handle('poki-helper:…', …)` that call into `helper.js`.
3. **`PokiHelper - Electron/preload.js`** — add matching methods on `contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('pokiHelper', { … })` using `ipcRenderer.invoke` with the **same** channel names as `main.js`.
4. **`PokiHelper - Angular/src/poki-helper-preload.d.ts`** — extend `PokiHelperPreload` (and `Window`) typings.
5. **`PokiHelper - Angular/src/app/Services/electron-helper.ts`** — add delegating method(s) on `ElectronHelper` that call `this.api().…` (mirror every exported helper function).

Coordinate pick (`waitForNextClickCoordinates`) is implemented in **`PokiHelper - Electron/coordinate-pick-overlay.js`** (+ `coordinate-pick-overlay.html`, `coordinate-pick-preload.js`) and wired from `main.js` / `preload.js` / typings / `ElectronHelper` — not in `helper.js`.

Do not add a helper only in Angular or only in Electron: **always** keep `helper.js` and `electron-helper.ts` (plus preload, IPC, and d.ts) aligned. Use consistent IPC channel names: `poki-helper:<kebab-action>`.
